column4: Hello!! today i got some important update at Update Manager but i got this ERROR, anyone help? http://paste.ubuntu.com/364950/
why? what does overclocking mean, i just installed the "IMPORTANT" updates via update manager
It's either a hardware problem or you downloaded your program wrong.
No, your RAM may be faulty.
how can i download again the file and reinstall it?
sudo apt-get autoclean if you can do that.
cant do that i got this error: E: dpkg was interrupted, you must manually run 'sudo dpkg --configure -a' to correct the problem.
and when i do dpkg --configure -a i got the Error on the pastebin page
ok ill do that, well c-ya later
If you see red then your memory is broken.
